@bessbd It seems I was too enthusiastic when I tried to replace `./mvnw clean install -DskipTests` with `./mvnw clean install` in `.travis.yml`. Trying to build all modules often times out. So I reduced the tested modules to the _most important/interesting ones_
The last build passed: https://travis-ci.com/github/apache/flume/builds/221898498
Now a new one runs after the Git squashes. Now with the warmed Maven cache at Travis I hope that any following build won't timeout, but let's see!
